<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1907-06-29T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1907-06-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="604" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d604">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 711.654/1–3.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to Ambassador <persName type="to">Griscom</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 47.]</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1907-06-29">
                                    <hi rend="italic">June 29, 1907</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge the receipt of your
                            despatch No. 82, of the 5th instant, with reference to the proposed
                            naturalization treaty between the United States and Italy.</p>
                        <p>This Government notes with great gratification the encouraging reception
                            of its proposition looking to a naturalization convention between the
                            two countries, and you will avail yourself of the earliest opportunity
                            to so inform the Minister of Foreign Relations.</p>
                        <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Alvey A. Adee</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>